    <briefdescription>
<para>Adds a suffix to the filename of a given file path. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Adds a suffix to the filename of a given file path.This function appends a given suffix to the stem (base name without extension) of a file while preserving the original directory and file extension.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>file_path</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The original file path. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>suffix</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The suffix to append to the filename. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>A new std::filesystem::path with the modified filename.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>If the input file has no extension, the suffix is added directly to the filename.</para>
</simplesect>
<programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/>std::filesystem::path<sp/>path<sp/>=<sp/></highlight><highlight class="stringliteral">&quot;example.txt&quot;</highlight><highlight class="normal">;</highlight></codeline>
